I'm always looking for the practical points.

Here's how he says to get a more Tiger like Dock:
-----------------------------------
If you want the alternate look when the Dock is on the bottom too,
type the following commands at a Terminal prompt:
% defaults write com.apple.dock no-glass -boolean YES
% killall Dock
-----------------------------------

To undo the above(change the YES to NO):
-----------------------------------
% defaults write com.apple.dock no-glass -boolean NO
% killall Dock
-----------------------------------

William Janoch
wjan ... @gmail.com

P. S. I tested the undo so I could play with the &quot;Half Drop&quot; effect.
That's where if you only go half way down the icon it only highlights
for your file to &quot;Drop On&quot; a program for &quot;Open With&quot; functionality,
but if you go all the way down to the 3D shelf then you can &quot;Drop On&quot;
or &quot;Drop Between&quot;.

note: holding &lt;command&gt;&lt;option&gt; will allow you to force the &quot;Drop On&quot;
effect for &quot;Open With&quot; functionality of Apps that would otherwise
refuse to try opening the file.  This was important for me when
someone renamed jpg files to the zip extention before emailing to me
to get it through a corporate spam catcher.  I'd just drag that image
to Preview and force it to try opening it.
